      <h1>Architecture of Causal Learner</h1>
      <span>
        Figure 2 illustrates the hierarchical architecture of Causal Learner, in which we also compare it with another toolbox for learning causal structure and MB, Causal Explorer. Generally, Causal Explorer only provides some algorithms, and it was developed 10 years ago, many new algorithms on learning causal structure and MB have been proposed. By contrast, Causal Learner conceives a more ambitious blueprint. It attempts to support the entire causal structure and MB learning procedure including data generation, state-of-the-art algorithms, and algorithm evaluations.
      </span>
      <br>
      <div class="img1">
        <img src="/img/Architecture.jpg">
        <br>
        <p>Figure 2: Architecture</p>
      </div>
      
    </div>
    <div>
      <h1>Data</h1>
      <span>
        In data layer, Causal Learner generates two types of data: discrete data and continuous 
        data. The data are simulated from various benchmark BNs (written in R language), and the details of each BN are shown in Table 1. The data can already be generated by the bnlearn toolbox, but the generated data is encapsulated in R language classes and cannot be easily used by researchers. The work that we have done is to output the generated data into text for easy use.
        <br>  
      </span>
