    </div>
    <div>
      <h1>Algorithm</h1>
      <span>
        In algorithm layer, Causal Learner implements 7 global causal structure learning algorithms, 4 local causal structure learning algorithms, and 15 MB learning algorithms (written in Matlab). Table 2 gives a list of all algorithms. To ensure the correctness of the algorithms we implement, 1) Unless the original implementations of algorithms are not released, we always try to integrate the original versions rather than re-implementing them. 2) Using the same data and evaluation functions, the algorithms in Causal Learner are comparable with that of Causal Explorer in accuracy, and achieve far better efficiency. 
      </span>
      <div class="img1">
        <img src="/img/Algorithms.png">
        <br>
        <p>Table 2: Algorithms (Learner represents Causal Learner and Explorer denotes Causal Explorer, • indicates that there is an algorithm in the corresponding toolbox, while ◦ indicates that the algorithm is not in the toolbox.)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
      <h1>Evaluation</h1>
      <span>
        In evaluation layer, Causal Learner provides abundant evaluation metrics for evaluating causal structure and MB learning algorithms (written in Matlab). In terms of accuracy, global and local causal structure learning algorithms use the same 7 metrics: Ar_F1, Ar_precision, Ar_recall, SHD, Miss, Extra, and Reverse, MB learning algorithms use 3 metrics: Adj_F1, Adj_precision, and Adj_recall. In terms of effiffifficiency, global causal structure learning algorithms use running time, while local causal structure and MB learning algorithms use the number of conditional independence tests and running time.
      </span>
